    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Agencies Selected For 2 Accounts</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Stuart Elliott</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Elliott, Stuart</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ask Jeeves names San Francisco office of Grey Worldwide; spending estimated at $50 million; Euro RSCG DSW Partners previously handled account; Wm Wrigley Jr Co names DDB Corbett to handle advertising for Surpass, new antacid chewing gum; billings estimated at $30 million (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Ask Jeeves, an online question-and-answer service, has named the San Francisco office of Grey Worldwide, part of the Grey Global Group, its agency of record. The San Francisco office of a Grey sibling, MediaCom, will handle media duties. Spending was estimated at $50 million. Euro RSCG DSW Partners in Salt Lake City, part of the Euro RSCG Worldwide unit of Havas Advertising, previously handled it.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Ask Jeeves, an online question-and-answer service, has named the San Francisco office of Grey Worldwide, part of the Grey Global Group, its agency of record. The San Francisco office of a Grey sibling, MediaCom, will handle media duties. Spending was estimated at $50 million. Euro RSCG DSW Partners in Salt Lake City, part of the Euro RSCG Worldwide unit of Havas Advertising, previously handled it.</p>
        <p>And the Wm. Wrigley Jr. Company named DDB Corbett in Chicago, a joint venture of two Chicago offices of the Omnicom Group -- Frank J. Corbett and DDB Worldwide -- to handle Surpass, a new antacid chewing gum. Billings were estimated at $30 million.</p>
        <p>THE MEDIA BUSINESS: ADVERTISING -- ADDENDA</p>
      </block>
